  "remarks": "Isle of Man-administered company that controls ship-owning companies in Hong Kong. The ships are operated by Safiran Payam Darya Shipping Lines (SAPID) which took over IRISL’s bulk services and routes and uses vessels previously owned by IRISL. One shareholder is Mohammed Hossein Dajmar, the managing director of IRISL. The Hong Kong companies are: New Synergy Ltd, Partner Century Ltd, Sackville Holdings Ltd, Sanford Group and Sino Access Holdings. Technical Management of the vessels is carried out by sanctioned Soroush Saramin Asatir (SSA).",
